{
  "stem": "1169.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "It means, oh, God who examines the innermost recesses of the heart.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And this prayer, [SPEAKING HEBREW], was learned by heart.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "For weeks, we learned it, one from another, because this was the decision-- the unanimous decision-- of the rabbis.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "And the implication, also, was that we have no words.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "Because we have no prayer books, we cannot speak.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "So God has to look into our hearts, instead of listening to prayers.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "Also, we found out that the Polish camp next to us has a shofar.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "And had no-- they were like slaves.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "They had no privileges at all.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "We made a deal with them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 60,
      "text": "We collected 200 cigarettes to obtain the shofar from the Polish camp.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 61,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] Then came the high holidays.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 62,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And the Holy Rabbi of Satu Mare, he prayed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 63,
      "text": "He had that only prayer book.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 64,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When we came to that segment of [SPEAKING HEBREW], God, look into our hearts, and you will understand our troubles, everybody cried.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 65,
      "text": "And everybody said it with great fervor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 66,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then came the blowing of the shofar.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 67,
      "text": "And the holy Rabbi of Satu Mare, he blew the shofar.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 68,
      "text": "I stood at the window of the barracks where we prayed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 69,
      "text": "I remember it like today.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 70,
      "text": "I don't think it was my imagination, but those walls of those barracks shook.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 71,
      "text": "They really trembled.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 72,
      "text": "It was so charged, the atmosphere.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 73,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And I look out the window from these barracks, and across I see a big truck being pushed-- and I counted-- by about 19 Polish Jews.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 74,
      "text": "This was the German way of torturing people-- to load up an empty truck with junk, make people take it someplace, empty it, and then take it back.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
